Example 22 (37th Canadian Mathematical Olympiad) If an ordered triplet of positive integers $\{a, b, c\}$ satisfies $a \leqslant b \leqslant c, (a, b, c)=1, a^{n}+b^{n}+c^{n}$ is divisible by $a+b+c$, then $\{a, b, c\}$ is called $n$-energetic. For example, $\{1, 2, 2\}$ is 5-energetic.
